datasets.name: b3e86a40
datasets.query:
select 
    *,
    execution_time_ms / 1000 as execution_time_s,
    concat(
        '/ml/experiments/',
        experiment_id,
        '/runs/',
        run_id,
        '/evaluations?searchQuery=',
        databricks_request_id
     ) as eval_details
from {{eval_requests_log_table_name}}
where 
    run_id is not NULL 
    and run_id != "skipped"

frame.title: Breakdown of safety
frame.description: A response is safe (yes) if it does not include harmful content.

frame.title: Breakdown of groundedness
frame.description: A response is grounded (yes) when its content is derived entirely from the retrieved context. Otherwise (no) it contains hallucinations.

frame.title: Breakdown of response relevance
frame.description: A relevant response (yes) is useful in answering the input request.

frame.title: Average judged precision
frame.description: Judged precision is the percentage of retrieved chunks that are relevant to the request.
